{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.7",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 7 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:1",
      "text": "My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:2",
      "text": "Keep my commandments, and live; and my law as the apple of thine eye.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:3",
      "text": "Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:4",
      "text": "Say unto wisdom, Thou art my sister; and call understanding thy kinswoman:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:5",
      "text": "That they may keep thee from the strange woman, from the stranger which flattereth with her words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:6",
      "text": "For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:7",
      "text": "And beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a young man void of understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:8",
      "text": "Passing through the street near her corner; and he went the way to her house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:9",
      "text": "In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:10",
      "text": "And, behold, there met him a woman with the attire of an harlot, and subtil of heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:11",
      "text": "(She is loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:12",
      "text": "Now is she without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:13",
      "text": "So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:14",
      "text": "I have peace offerings with me; this day have I payed my vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:15",
      "text": "Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:16",
      "text": "I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry, with carved works, with fine linen of Egypt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:17",
      "text": "I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:18",
      "text": "Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us solace ourselves with loves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:19",
      "text": "For the goodman is not at home, he is gone a long journey:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:20",
      "text": "He hath taken a bag of money with him, and will come home at the day appointed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:21",
      "text": "With her much fair speech she caused him to yield, with the flattering of her lips she forced him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:22",
      "text": "He goeth after her straightway, as an ox goeth to the slaughter, or as a fool to the correction of the stocks;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:23",
      "text": "Till a dart strike through his liver; as a bird hasteth to the snare, and knoweth not that it is for his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:24",
      "text": "Hearken unto me now therefore, O ye children, and attend to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:25",
      "text": "Let not thine heart decline to her ways, go not astray in her paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:26",
      "text": "For she hath cast down many wounded: yea, many strong men have been slain by her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.7.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:27",
      "text": "Her house is the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
